{
  "title": "VimFu — Vim Regex Syntax",
  "description": "Vim regex escaping rules: \\+ \\? \\(\\) \\| \\<\\> must be escaped, unlike PCRE regex.",
  "speed": 0.55,
  "rows": 20,
  "cols": 40,
  "humanize": 0.7,
  "seed": 816,
  "ttsVoice": "echo",
  "playlist": "VimFu",
  "tags": ["vim", "neovim", "nvim", "vimfu", "tutorial", "terminal", "editor", "coding", "programming", "ex commands"],
  "setup": [
    { "comment": "Set TERM for proper color support in Neovim" },
    { "line": "export TERM=xterm-256color" },
    { "comment": "Prepare workspace" },
    { "line": "mkdir -p ~/vimfu && cd ~/vimfu" },
    { "line": "rm -f demo.txt .demo.txt.swp .demo.txt.swo" },
    { "line": "find ~/.local/state/nvim/swap -mindepth 1 -delete 2>/dev/null" },
    { "comment": "Create demo file" },
    { "writeFile": "demo.txt", "content": "cat cats\ndog dogs\nthe bat batted\nhat hats hatted" },
    { "line": "clear" },
    { "comment": "Launch nvim" },
    { "line": "nvim demo.txt" },
    { "waitForScreen": "All", "timeout": 30.0 },
    { "ifScreen": "swap file", "thenKeys": "d" }
  ],
  "steps": [
    { "comment": "--- Title card ---" },
    { "overlay": "VimFu", "caption": "Vim Regex Syntax", "duration": 2.0 },
    { "wait": 0.5 },
    { "comment": "--- Intro ---" },
    { "say": "Vim regex is different from modern regex. Some special characters need a backslash. Let's cover the key differences." },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "comment": "--- Demo: \\+ for one or more ---" },
    { "say": "Backslash plus means one or more. In most regex it's just plus. In Vim you need the backslash." },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "type": ":set hlsearch" },
    "enter",
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "type": "/\\w\\+", "overlay": "/\\w\\+ (one or more)" },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    "enter",
    { "wait": 0.8 },
    { "comment": "--- Demo: \\< \\> word boundary ---" },
    { "say": "Backslash angle brackets match word boundaries. Find the exact word cat, not cats.", "wait": false },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "type": "/\\<cat\\>", "overlay": "/\\<cat\\> (word boundary)" },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    "enter",
    { "wait": 0.8 },
    { "say": "Only cat matched, not cats. Word boundaries are powerful." },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "comment": "--- Demo: \\| for alternation ---" },
    { "say": "Backslash pipe means or. Match cat or dog.", "wait": false },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    { "type": "/cat\\|dog", "overlay": "/cat\\|dog (or)" },
    { "wait": 0.3 },
    "enter",
    { "wait": 0.8 },
    { "comment": "--- Wrap up ---" },
    { "say": "Vim regex. Backslash plus for one or more, backslash question for optional, backslash parens for groups, backslash pipe for or, backslash angle brackets for word boundaries. Different from Perl but just as powerful." },
    { "wait": 1.5 }
  ],
  "teardown": [
    { "comment": "Quit nvim without saving" },
    "escape",
    { "type": ":q!" },
    "enter",
    { "line": "rm -f demo.txt" }
  ]
}
